reviews.review_text: Listen to it first The only songs I checked out were Truckin' and U.S. Blues.  Bob's voice is not good singing lead vocals for Truckin'.  However, Jerry sounds fine on U.S. Blues, Bob is OK on background voc., and the whole band played it well.  Suggest you listen to a few other songs before downloading whole concert.

great quality recording The previous reviewer was making his opinion on how bobby sounded on playin.... Well that has nothing to do w/this recording. The original taper had some great equipment, early digital(pcm) MASTER recordings made w/neumann mics and equip. which means that said taper did his or her best to complete this recording w/ some of the best equip.avail at the time If there is flaws and there very well could be it most likely came from the mix cause it sure wasn't for lack of trying by taper.
Audible this is an amazing AUD recording from 1986. and now since archive has lost sbds it is shows such as this that matter!!!

When I listened for the first time I imediatly went for might as well, followed by crazy fingers,then loser. It was then that I  felt that there was the deciding factor, bobby always messes up truckin but jerry playin might as well is better than a perfect truckin anyday IMO!!!!!!
